text:
201 Columbia Heights, at the N.E. corner of Pierrepont Street, showing the home of Seth Low who was born at No. 165 (now 189) Washington Street, on January 18, 1850. He was elected Mayor of Brooklyn in 1881. This house owned by James Humphreys, a republican, who was a member of Congress during the Civil War, was sold to Mr. Seth Low who modernized it. The house was razed in May 1924.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

text:
(1) 220-222 Columbia Heights, at the N.W. corner of Columbia Heights and Pierrepont Street. The house at the left was that of Peter C. Cornell and later that of David H. Leggett. The house at the right (No. 220) belonged to John Bullet, and at one time was occupied by Henry K. Shelton.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing a further view north.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
